body:
Jump pt 2: Anpanman

In a similar way to the way the lyrics to “I’m Fine” link to “Save Me”, I think that Anpanman links to Jump

In Jump, Suga raps

“The hero you’ve dreamed of since you were young

We used to jump, wanting to be heroes

…

To the times when the 10-year-old boy sang the theme song to his favorite superhero comic”

And then in Anpanman, he says

“I’ve dreamed of becoming a hero like Superman

I ran with all my strength, jumping high up in the sky

I’m not afraid of little things like bruising my knees

The innocent fantasies of my childhood

//

I can be your hero”

They wanted to be superheroes and they became our heroes

summary: BTS' Fake Love Most Streamed K-Pop Song Ever on Spotify
title: BTS' Fake Love Most Streamed K-Pop Song Ever on Spotify
excerpt: The New Year has barely started and BTS is already breaking new records! Media outlet 'Forbes' has reported that BTS' top song 'Fake Love', has become the most-streamed song ever on the major music streaming service, 'Spotify', by any K-Pop artist ever! With over 184 millions streams in the seven months since its release 'Fake Love' has beat out Psy's 'Gangnam Style' while BTS themselves are among the most streamed groups of 2018 - second only to 'Imagine Dragons'.
